    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Platform medic treated laceration with ice and over-the-counter pain medication",
      "IP evacuated to Lafayette General Medical Center on 11 October 2021",
      "Medical evaluation revealed laceration requiring five sutures and hairline fracture",
      "Pin insertion planned for hairline fracture with 4-6 weeks recovery time",
      "BSEE onsite follow-up investigation conducted on 14 October 2021"
    ],
    "summary": "On 10 October 2021 at 2045 hours, a Halliburton employee sustained a laceration and hairline fracture to his left-hand middle finger while installing a 6-inch bail into a swivel becket during hydraulic workover unit operations on Well B001 at Shell's Salsa Platform. The injury occurred when the swivel becket moved unexpectedly due to the pin being in the locked open position, causing the bail to slide downward and impact the pneumatic back saver, pinching the employee's finger between the bail and the back saver.",
    "recommendations": [],
